cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for 3D layout recovery of indoor scenes using a combination of geometric reasoning and deep learning techniques. The paper focuses on computer vision and robotics applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves geometric reasoning and pattern recognition, which could also make it relevant to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
